<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">22.01.2026</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The concept and development of health tourism; the concept of medical tourism; senior (elderly) and disabled tourism; and the concepts of thermal tourism. The concept of reverse flow in medical tourism; the concepts of tourism health and tourist health, and their differences from the concept of medical tourism. The most common treatment areas sought by medical tourists and the countries they prefer, along with the reasons for the development of medical tourism. The role of Asian countries in medical tourism; cross-border patient mobility observed in European countries and its relationship with the concept of medical tourism. Medical tourism activities in the American continent.Medical tourism activities in the American continent.</Data></Cell>
